clone 1 clone 2 deseq2 analysis

Cindy Liang (celiang@ucsc.edu)

April 03, 2025

Introduction:

poly(A)-selected RNA from two isogenic clones of human bronchial epithelial cells (HBECs) were sequenced with the Illumina NovaSeq S4 (PE150). Following alignment to a modified version of the GRCh38 reference genome that makes the U2AF1 alignable (Miller 2022) with STAR, HTSeq-count was run on the aligned files to produce gene count files.

In this notebook, the DESeq2 and limma packages are used to collapse technical replicates in clone 1, batch correct clone 1 and clone 2 samples, and plot PCAs of the DESeq2 matrices before and after batch correction.

Please see the projects biorxiv and github repo for further method details.

Construct deseq dataset

u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq<-DESeqDataSetFromHTSeqCount(sampleTable=u2af1krassampleTable, directory=htseqcount_dir, design= ~batch + condition)
Warning: some variables in design formula are characters, converting to factors
# collapse technical replicates of clone 1

u2af1krasddsColl <-collapseReplicates(u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq, u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq$sample, u2af1kras_ddsHTSeq$run)

# set wt lacz as control
u2af1krasddsColl$condition <- relevel(u2af1krasddsColl$condition, ref = 'U2AF1_WT_LACZ')
